1. Install sbt
--------------

Install sbt; see http://www.scala-sbt.org/download.html for instructions.

2. Get the source
----------

Run

git clone https://bitbucket.org/jkatelaan/harrsh.git
cd harrsh

3. Compile & run
------

You can now run HARRSH via the provided shell script

./harrsh.sh --help

The first time, this will fetch dependencies and compile the source code, which might take several minutes.

4. Update
---------

To update to a newer revision, simply run

git pull

The next time you invoke harrsh.sh, the code will be recompiled automatically.